column1: Target username "isaDiva" is associated with User ID "f1a2b3c4-d5e6-f7a8-b9c0-d1e2f3a4b5c6"
Date range searched: Jan 01 2023 00:00:00 UTC - Jan 01 2025 00:00:00 UTC
content_type: The type of content sent in the communication such as AudioSnap, Text, ExternalMedia, Sticker, VoiceNote, etc
message_type: The type of message sent in the communication. The value will always be "Snap" or "Chat"
conversation_id: The universally unique identifier ("UUID") for the one-to-one or group conversation

message_id: A non-unique identifier that increases with each message in the particular conversation. (Note: The assigned numerical value does not necessarily indicate the volume of previously exchanged messages.)
reply_to_message_id: The message_id of the message that this message replies to, if this message was a reply
conversation_title: The name of the group conversation. If blank, the group conversation has not been named or is a one-to-one conversation
sender_username: The username of the account that sent the message
sender_user_id: The user ID of the account that sent the message. The UUID is provided in string format
recipient_username: The one-to-one username of the account that was the recipient of the message. This is not used for group conversations
recipient_user_id: The user ID of the account that received the message. The UUID is provided in string format
text: The text of a chat message
media_id: The internal ID number for the media file
is_saved: "TRUE" if the communications content is saved in the messaging conversation. "FALSE" if it is not saved
is_one_on_one: "TRUE" if this is a one-to-one conversation. "FALSE" if this is a group conversation
timestamp: The timestamp of when the action was performed on Snapchat, the action could be sending a message or setting a wallpaper.
group_member_usernames: The username(s) of the account(s) that were part of this group when the message was sent AND are still in this group when the request for this data is submitted
group_member_user_ids: The user ID(s) of the account(s) that were part of this group when the message was sent AND are still in this group when the request for this data is submitted

reactions: The reactions from users to this message. It can contain one or more reactions, and each single reaction is {user_id}-{reaction_integer}. The reaction integer is defined as: 1 for Love, 2 for Laugh Cry, 3 for Fire, 4 for Thumbs Up, 5 for Thumbs Down, 6 for Sad Cry, 7 for Wow.
saved_by: The user ID(s) of the account(s) that saved the content to chat. The UUID is provided in string format
screenshotted_by: The user ID(s) of the account(s) that have screenshotted the content. The UUID is provided in string format
replayed_by: The user ID(s) of the account(s) that replayed the content. The UUID is provided in string format
screen_recorded_by: The user ID(s) of the account(s) that have screen recorded the content. The UUID is provided in string format
read_by: The user ID(s) of the account(s) that viewed the content. The UUID is provided in string format
chat_wallpaper_setter_id: The user ID of the account that set the wallpaper
upload_ip: IP address associated with the media upload. Upload IPs may be available for some Snapchat media. When upload IPs are available, they will appear in this field.
source_port_number: The source port number associated with the IP address of the media upload.

column11: text
Did anyone else notice the time for the 'Starlight' callback was... adjusted? Just curious.
Adjusted how- darling? Some of us have packed schedules. Punctuality is a virtue.

Oh! I'm sure it was just a simple mistake. Casting directors are just SO overwhelmed. It's not like anyone would intentionally try to get an earlier slot to throw others off. That would be terribly unprofessional.
Exactly Isabella! That's what I thought too. It's just... my agent got the updated time at 3 AM. Seemed odd is all. But I'm sure Julian's agent was just being extra diligent for him! So thoughtful.
This discourse is irrelevant. The art cares not for your temporal squabbles. I am currently communing with the spirit of the character. Please do not disturb my process with such trivialities.
Julian. A word. Your 'improvisation' in our scene today was... a choice.
Isabella. My love! I was simply feeling the moment. The character is meant to be unpredictable. No? I thought it added a wonderful spark.
The "spark" nearly set my wig on fire. Remember, dear boy, this is a dance. We are partners. It is not a solo performance. The camera needs to know where to look.
Of course. My only goal is to elevate the scene. And you. I would never dream of pulling focus. Your close-up is safe. For now.
Dominic, darling. Julian Vance. Just following up on the "Starlight" lead. I feel such a connection to the material.
Julian. Good to hear from you. The competition is... fierce. We're looking for an actor with true, palpable dedication.
I can assure you that my dedication is limitless. I'm willing to do whatever it takes to truly understand the role. Private coaching and extra rehearsals... you name it.
Let's talk offline. My office, tomorrow. 8 PM. We can discuss the... nuances... of the character. Come alone.
Can anyone tell me if this is champagne or sparkling cider? My palate is insulted.
Forget the drinks. Did you SEE Julian schmoozing with Dominic? He hasn't left his side all night. I guess his ""dedication"" really paid off.
Some people just have a talent for... networking. It's a very specific skill set. Not everyone has the stomach for it.
Chloe. I've been watching your career. Such talent. It's a shame to see it wasted.
I'm sorry but who is this?
A friend. Let's just say I know how the game is really played. Talent gets you in the room. Other... arrangements... get you the part. I facilitate those arrangements.
What kind of arrangements?

The kind that ensures the right people are happy. It requires an investment, of course. But the return is a guaranteed role. Think of it as a private audition with a guaranteed callback. Interested in meeting a producer I know? He's very... hands-on.
I'm going to pretend I never saw this conversation. Don't contact me again.
Isabella, darling. Word on the street is you've been spreading some rather colorful stories about Julian's... methods. How very unprofessional of you.

Valentina! How lovely to hear from you. I simply share what I observe. If Julian finds the truth uncomfortable, perhaps he should reconsider his choices. The industry thrives on authenticity, don't you think?

Authenticity? Is that what we're calling jealousy now? Julian got the part because he's talented. Not everyone can accept when they've been outperformed. Perhaps you should focus on your own audition technique rather than analyzing others'.

Outperformed? Oh my sweet, deluded Valentina. We both know there are many ways to "perform" in this business. Some require actual talent. Others require... flexibility. I'll let you guess which category your precious Julian falls into.
You're playing a dangerous game. Some secrets are better left buried. I'd hate for your own... creative choices... to come to light.

I'm absolutely DEVASTATED. After everything I put into the Ophelia audition - the months of preparation- the emotional journey - they gave it to that amateur from community theater. COMMUNITY THEATER! The world has gone mad.

Isabella darling... perhaps they were looking for someone with more... accessibility? You know how directors can be. They want someone they can mold. Your interpretation was probably too sophisticated for their vision.
The theater gods have spoken. Perhaps this is the universe telling you to pursue more... commercial endeavors. Not everyone is destined for classical tragedy. Some are meant for... lighter fare.
Marcus! How DARE you. Lighter fare? I am a classically trained artist! I have studied with the masters! I am not some bubble-headed ing√©nue destined for romantic comedies!

Bella sweetie... we all have our crosses to bear. Remember when I didn't get Lady Macbeth? I channeled that pain into my one-woman show about the forgotten wives of Shakespeare. Sometimes rejection is redirection. Maybe it's time for you to... reinvent yourself?
I hate to be that person but... didn't Isabella miss two of the callback sessions? I mean I'm sure she had very valid reasons but... punctuality does matter in this business...

Chloe! I was dealing with a family emergency! My grandmother was in the hospital! Some things are more important than auditions! Though I wouldn't expect someone who's never booked anything significant to understand the weight of real responsibility!
Never booked anything significant? I'm literally starring in the new indie film that's getting Oscar buzz. But sure Isabella. Attack everyone else instead of looking in the mirror.

Ladies... LADIES. This is exactly why they don't take us seriously. We're tearing each other apart instead of supporting one another. The industry is hard enough without us making it harder on each other.
Seraphina is right. We should be lifting each other up. Isabella... I know this hurts. But maybe use this energy for your next audition? Channel that rage into Lady Macbeth or Medea?
You know what? You're all right. I'm sorry. This rejection just... it cut deep. I put everything into that audition. But attacking each other won't get any of us closer to our dreams.
The artist's journey is paved with rejection. Each 'no' brings us closer to our destined 'yes'. This pain... it is the crucible in which greatness is forged. Embrace it. Let it transform you.
Marcus... that was actually beautiful. And Isabella - your vulnerability just now? That was more real than any monologue. THAT is the authenticity directors are looking for.
Group hug! Virtually speaking. We're all in this crazy business together. Next round of auditions we should support each other instead of... well... this drama fest we just had.
Agreed! Though let's be honest... we'll probably be back to our passive-aggressive ways by tomorrow. It's who we are. But at least now we know we care about each other underneath all the drama.
Seraphina speaking the hard truths! Fine. Tomorrow we'll be back to our usual suspects routine. But tonight... tonight we're family. A very dysfunctional theater family.
Wait. Did anyone else get the email about the emergency workshop tomorrow? For the Shakespeare intensive? They're only taking 12 people and applications are due at midnight.
Marcus... what email? I didn't get anything. Are you sure you're on the right mailing list? Or... is this one of those invitation-only things?

I didn't get it either. Marcus... are you SURE this is real? Because if this is some elaborate prank to get us all worked up and scrambling to write applications... that would be very unlike you. But also brilliant.
OH MY GOD. I just checked my spam folder. It's there! It's REAL! And it's from Helena Ravencroft! THE Helena Ravencroft! She's only the most prestigious acting coach in the city!
Helena Ravencroft? Wait. The woman who trained Daniel Day-Lewis for his Lincoln prep? The one who charges $500 an hour and has a waiting list longer than Hamilton tickets? That Helena Ravencroft?
OMG checking my spam now too... Found it! This is insane! The application requires a 30-second monologue video AND a personal statement about our deepest theatrical truth. In less than 2 hours!

And now the claws come out... Again. We literally just had this beautiful moment of solidarity and now we're about to turn into gladiators fighting over 12 spots. I can already feel the passive aggression brewing.
Isabella's right. But also... may the best actor win? I'm already mentally preparing my Lady Macbeth sleepwalking scene. It's my strongest piece and I've been perfecting it for months.
Val... everyone does Lady Macbeth sleepwalking scene. It's like the monologue equivalent of wearing a little black dress to a fashion show. Safe but not memorable. Just saying.
Chloe sweetie... that was unnecessarily harsh. But also... not wrong. I'm thinking of doing Viola's ring speech from Twelfth Night. It's got the gender fluidity angle that's very now.
I shall perform Hamlet's 'To be or not to be' but as interpreted through the lens of modern existential dread and social media anxiety. It's a bold fusion of classical text and contemporary angst.
Marcus... darling... that sounds very pretentious even by your standards. Helena Ravencroft values authenticity over concept. I'm doing Portia's mercy speech. Classic. Powerful. Relevant.
I'm doing something none of you would expect. Beatrice from Much Ado. The 'Kill Claudio' scene. Pure fury. Pure power. And completely unexpected from me. Sometimes you have to surprise people.
Isabella... that's... actually brilliant. Okay I'm rethinking my Lady Macbeth choice. Maybe I need to go deeper into the weird sisters? Something more... unhinged?
Marcus... can I ask you something personal? In private? About your workshop application... I have some thoughts.

Seraphina. Of course. Though I must warn you, I am in a deeply meditative state preparing for my performance. Your thoughts are welcome, but I cannot guarantee they will penetrate the artistic trance I've entered.

Marcus... sweetie... your social media anxiety interpretation of Hamlet? It's going to read as gimmicky. Helena Ravencroft despises gimmicks. She wants to see the actor, not the concept. Maybe just... be Marcus? Raw and vulnerable Marcus?

You... you think I should abandon my artistic vision? My interpretation? But Seraphina, without the concept, I'm just another actor doing Hamlet. The concept IS what makes it unique. What makes it... me.

Marcus... YOU are what makes it unique. Your depth, your intelligence, your genuine passion. Trust that. Sometimes the most powerful choice is to strip everything away and just... be truthful. Helena will see through any artifice instantly.

Adrianne! Emergency. I just saw your Instagram story about the Helena workshop. Did you REALLY have to post yourself practicing Portia in full costume and professional lighting? We all agreed to keep this low-key!

Chloe darling, when did we agree to keep it low-key? I'm simply sharing my artistic journey with my followers. Social media IS part of building a brand. Helena probably follows me anyway - this is just showing my dedication.

Your "artistic journey"? You mean your desperate attempt to influence Helena's decision before she even sees the applications? That's not dedication, that's manipulation. And it's beneath you. Or at least I thought it was.

Manipulation? Chloe, that's a very ugly word. I prefer "strategic positioning." We're all adults here. Helena will choose based on talent, not social media presence. If you're threatened by my... proactive approach... maybe you should examine your own insecurities.
Valentina, my darling nemesis. I heard through the grapevine that you didn't get into Helena's workshop. Such a pity. I'm sure it was... competitive.
Julian. How thoughtful of you to check in. Yes, I didn't get in. Neither did you, I assume? Since you're here gloating instead of... oh, I don't know... preparing for the intensive?

Actually, my dear, I DID get in. That's why I'm reaching out. Professional courtesy, you understand. I thought you should hear it from me rather than through the theater gossip mill. Helena was quite impressed with my raw vulnerability.
Your "raw vulnerability"? Is that what we're calling your particular brand of networking now? Congratulations, Julian. I'm sure you'll learn so much. About acting. Specifically.
EVERYONE. Emergency meeting. Virtual or in person. NOW. Helena just announced the workshop results and there's been some... interesting developments that we need to discuss. IMMEDIATELY.
Isabella you're scaring me. What happened? Did Julian not actually get in? Please tell me he lied about getting accepted because that would honestly restore my faith in the universe.

Oh ladies... you're going to hate this. I did get in. So did Marcus and Seraphina. But the real tea? Helena's assistant just called. Apparently someone's been spreading rumors about my... relationship... with Dominic. Helena's reconsidering my spot.

Julian... darling... I hope you're not implying that I had anything to do with those rumors. Because that would be a very serious accusation. And also very hypocritical considering your own... history... of strategic information sharing.

STOP. Both of you. This is exactly what I was afraid would happen. The industry is small enough without us destroying each other over a workshop. Julian - did Helena actually say she's reconsidering? Or is this just paranoia?

This is all becoming very unseemly. The art suffers when artists attack each other. Perhaps we should focus on the real question: who among us has the strength to rise above this petty drama and truly commit to the craft?

Marcus makes a good point. But Julian - you need to be honest with us. What exactly did Helena's assistant say? Word for word. Because if someone really is sabotaging you... that's not okay. Even if we all have... complicated feelings about your methods.

I can't believe I'm saying this but... Seraphina's right. Julian. we may have our differences but if someone is actively trying to destroy your career over personal relationships... that crosses a line. We need to know who we're dealing with.

Fine. Her assistant said... and I quote... 'Helena has received some concerning information about your professional conduct and feels it may reflect poorly on the workshop's reputation.' They want me to provide character references. PROFESSIONAL character references. From industry people.

That's... actually not that bad? I mean it's not great but they're giving you a chance to defend yourself. And honestly Julian... we can all provide character references. Whatever our personal drama... you're a talented actor. That part has never been in question.

Chloe's right. Julian... despite everything... you're one of the most dedicated actors I know. I'll write a reference. We may compete against each other but we don't destroy each other. That's not who we are.

I'm in too. We'll all write references. But Julian... this needs to be a wake-up call. Not about your talent - that's never been in question. But about... well... how you navigate the business side of things. Maybe it's time for a different approach?

You know what... you're all right. I've been so focused on getting ahead that I forgot about the people around me. Thank you. For the references- yes- but also for... this. For showing me that competition doesn't have to mean destruction. I owe you all apologies. Many apologies.

This... this is what true artistry looks like. Not the performing. This. The vulnerability. The honesty. The willingness to change. Julian- you've just given your best performance yet. Helena would be impressed.

Okay everyone. Group meeting next week to plan our collective world domination? Because if we can survive all this drama and still come together... we're unstoppable. And Julian? You get the workshop. We'll make sure of it.
World domination sounds perfect. But first - drinks? Real ones this time- not whatever that champagne disaster was at the premiere? We've earned it. All of us.

Drinks it is! And you know what? For the first time in months I'm actually excited about this crazy and dramatic and impossible industry we've chosen. Because we have each other. And that's... that's actually kind of beautiful.

Julian. I've received your character references. All seven of them. Quite impressive how quickly your colleagues rallied around you. It speaks well of your character, despite the... complications. Your spot is secure.

Helena. Thank you. I... I can't express how much this means to me. And you're right about my colleagues. They taught me something important about what really matters in this business. I won't let you down.
